---
title: Coconut Curry with Chickpea & Bell Pepper swirled with Yogurt & served with Basmati Rice
description: Curries are one of those meals that warm your heart and your belly, and tonight’s vegetarian version is no exception. Chickpeas, onion, and bell pepper get a super savory treatment in a coconut-based curry sauce. Toss that over rice, add a swirl of yogurt and a sprinkle of cilantro, and you have yourself one soul-satisfying meal.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/coconut-curry-with-chickpea-bell-pepper-a9ee009d.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/coconut-curry-with-chickpea-bell-pepper-60b78d33d040445a364cae04-504a8322.pdf
cuisine: Indian
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/coconut-curry-with-chickpea-bell-pepper-60b78d33d040445a364cae04
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 790 kcal
  fat: 34 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 99 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 18 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 920 mg
servings: 2
author: Michelle Doll Olson
---

Wash and dry all produce.

Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Halve, peel, and finely dice half the
@yellow onion{1}(diced). Core, deseed, and finely dice @bell pepper{1}(diced).
Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(chopped). Drain and rinse @chickpeas{13.4%ounce}.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the garlic
and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, ¾ cup water, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a
boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat.
Add onion and bell pepper; cook until softened and starting to brown,
~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir in @tomato paste{1.5%ounce}, @curry powder{1%tbsp}, @paprika{1%tsp}, half the
@garam masala{1%tsp}, and remaining garlic until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

> Love the earthy warmth of garam masala? Add more if you like!

Stir in chickpeas, @coconut milk{5.07%ounce}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, ¼ cup
water, and @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Bring to a simmer, reduce to low, and cook until
thickened, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> Add a splash of water if curry is too thick.

Remove from heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Season generously with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper. Divide between
#bowls{}.

Top with curry. Dollop with @yogurt{2%tbsp}. Garnish with cilantro. Serve.